sting, if rare, name. <i>Alma</i> is also the feminine form of the Latin adjective <i>almus</i> ‘nourishing, kind’ (compare the term <i>alma mater</i> ‘fostering mother’, denoting an educational establishment). The name was borne by  Alma Bennett  (  1889–1958 ), American vamp of the silent screen. In  Tennessee Williams's  play Summer and Smoke (  1948 ), a bearer of the name explains that it is ‘Spanish for soul’, but this seems to be no more than coincidental."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Amma De Grainsby was born about 1095, in Scotland as the daughter of End of line and End of line. She had at least 3 sons with Eimerus Galeius Walense le strange. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1095–":"umbes 1095–Surnud","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1123–1179":"1123–1179","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1117":"1117","Abt 1095":"umbes 1095","1179":"1179","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","about 1120":"umbes 1120","1180":"1180","Riccarton, Scotland":"Riccarton, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1095–":"noin 1095–Kuollut","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1123–1179":"1123–1179","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1117":"1117","Abt 1095":"noin 1095","1179":"1179","1123":"1123","1100":"1100","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","about 1120":"noin 1120","1180":"1180","Riccarton, Scotland":"Riccarton, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pontefract, Yorkshire, England":"Pontefract, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1095–":"environ 1095–Décédée","1095–Female":"1095–Décédée","1100–114